flightcontrolhq/superjson#310.body:
This package commits the cardinal sin of escaping: failing to fully exempt non-escaped input from unescaping (e.g., [`escapeKey`](https://github.com/flightcontrolhq/superjson/blob/0ac86f0ad70c9770471c1c4c4006b4e46381fa83/src/pathstringifier.ts#L4) escapes each `.` as `\.` but fails to escape `\` itself). As a result, there are some injection bugs: https://jsfiddle.net/euqLwk4r/

input
```js
({
  a: [ "/'a'[0]: string that becomes a regex/" ],
  'a.0': /'a.0': regex that becomes a string/,
  'b.0': "/'b.0': string that becomes a regex/",
  'b\\': [ /'b\\'[0]: regex that becomes a string/ ],
})
```
encodes to
```json
{
  "json": {
    "a": [ "/'a'[0]: string that becomes a regex/" ],
    "a.0": "/'a.0': regex that becomes a string/",
    "b.0": "/'b.0': string that becomes a regex/",
    "b\\": [ "/'b\\\\'[0]: regex that becomes a string/" ]
  },
  "meta": {
    "values": {
      "a.0": [ "regexp" ],
      "b\\.0": [ "regexp" ]
    }
  }
}
```
which decodes as the input-dissimilar
```js
({
  a: [ /'a'[0]: string that becomes a regex/ ],
  'a.0': "/'a.0': regex that becomes a string/",
  'b.0': /'b.0': string that becomes a regex/,
  'b\\': [ "/'b\\\\'[0]: regex that becomes a string/" ],
})
```

