### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe it

I have custom bootstrap function which works for nestjs 10:

```typescript
import { NestFactory } from '@nestjs/core'

export interface BootstrapOptions {
  // Enables the usage of shutdown hooks.
  enableShutdownHooks?: boolean;

  // Other options
}

export async function bootstrap<T>(appModule: T, options?: BootstrapOptions) {
  const app = await NestFactory.create<NestExpressApplication>(appModule);

  // Custom setup base on options
  // ...

  await app.listen(config.get<number>('PORT'));
  return app;
}
```

It accpets a appModule of type T as fist arguement, which was used immediately to call `NestFactory.create()`.

While upgrade to NestJS 11, the `NestFactory.create` hans change its first arguemnt type to `IEntryNestModule`, which breaks above code for types error.

So I need `IEntryNestModule` to be exported from `@nestjs/core`.


### Describe the solution you'd like

Export `IEntryNestModule` [defined here](https://github.com/nestjs/nest/blob/master/packages/core/nest-factory.ts#L34C6-L34C22).


### Teachability, documentation, adoption, migration strategy

Export one more typescript type will be a minor change.

### What is the motivation / use case for changing the behavior?

After `IEntryNestModule` been exported from `@nestjs/core`, my code above can be modifed as following:

```diff
-import { NestFactory } from '@nestjs/core';
+import { NestFactory, IEntryNestModule } from '@nestjs/core';

export interface BootstrapOptions {
  // Enables the usage of shutdown hooks.
  enableShutdownHooks?: boolean;

  // Other options
}

-export async function bootstrap<T>(appModule: T, options?: BootstrapOptions) {
+export async function bootstrap(appModule: IEntryNestModule, options?: BootstrapOptions) {
  const app = await NestFactory.create<NestExpressApplication>(appModule);

  // Custom setup base on options
  // ...

  await app.listen(config.get<number>('PORT'));
  return app;
}
```
